[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bin lorry driver charged over Dunblane OAP death crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A bin lorry driver has been charged with causing death by careless and inconsiderate driving after a crash with an 80-year-old man in an electric wheelchair.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Peter Wills died at the scene of the crash in Sheriffmuir Road, Dunblane, on 3 December.
Police said the 42-year-old driver was charged following "extensive inquiries" by the Stirling road policing unit.
The man will appear in court at a later date.
